Psalms 15.text:
He who doesn’t slander with his tongue,
nor does evil to his friend,
nor casts slurs against his fellow man;

In whose eyes a vile man is despised,
but who honors those who fear Yahweh;
he who keeps an oath even when it hurts, and doesn’t change;

Psalms 17.text:
Arise, Yahweh, confront him.
Cast him down.
Deliver my soul from the wicked by your sword;

Psalms 18.text:
Yahweh is my rock, my fortress, and my deliverer;
my God, my rock, in whom I take refuge;
my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my high tower.

Psalms 19.text:
His going out is from the end of the heavens,
his circuit to its ends;
There is nothing hidden from its heat.

Psalms 22.text:
For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted,
Neither has he hidden his face from him;
but when he cried to him, he heard.

Psalms 24.text:
He who has clean hands and a pure heart;
who has not lifted up his soul to falsehood,
and has not sworn deceitfully.

Lift up your heads, you gates;
yes, lift them up, you everlasting doors,
and the King of glory will come in.

Psalms 31.text:
For I have heard the slander of many, terror on every side,
while they conspire together against me,
they plot to take away my life.

Psalms 85.text:
I will hear what God, Yahweh, will speak,
for he will speak peace to his people, his saints;
but let them not turn again to folly.

Psalms 90.text:
Let the favor of the Lord our God be on us;
establish the work of our hands for us;
yes, establish the work of our hands.

Psalms 91.text:
A thousand may fall at your side,
and ten thousand at your right hand;
but it will not come near you.

Psalms 99.text:
Moses and Aaron were among his priests,
Samuel among those who call on his name;
they called on Yahweh, and he answered them.

